# Embedding model registry-delivery matrix

## Scope

This matrix covers the embedding options evaluated for the GoTo project under
one unusual but strict constraint: the DevPod can download packages only through
its approved NPM and PyPI/`uv` proxies. It cannot download model files directly
from Hugging Face, GitHub releases, or arbitrary CDNs.

The ✅ column means that the registry artifact itself contains the model weights.
A ❌ means that installing the package provides inference code but a separate
model download is still required. Only ✅ rows are immediately usable under the
current DevPod policy.

Dates use `DD.MM.YYYY`. They refer to the model artifact or port listed in the
row, not to the latest release of the surrounding inference library. Sizes are
model-weight sizes, not Python/JavaScript library sizes. When weights are fused
with an engine inside WASM and cannot be separated, the WASM container size is
reported explicitly.

